Step 1: Clone the repository 🖥️
Start by cloning the repo to your local machine. Run the following command in your terminal:

bash
git clone https://github.com/klukvinM/scrouch-.git
Step 2: Set up a virtual environment ⚙️
Move to the backend directory and create a virtual environment:

bash
cd backend
python -m venv venv
Then activate it:

Windows:
bash
venv\Scripts\activate
macOS/Linux:
bash
source venv/bin/activate
Step 3: Install required packages 📦
Make sure you're inside the backend directory and virtual environment is activated. Then install all the required dependencies:

bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
Step 4: Start the backend server 🚀
Start the FastAPI backend server:

bash
uvicorn main:app --reload
Step 5: Open the app in your browser 🌐
Open your browser and navigate to:

http://localhost:8000/docs

Step 6: Start posture detection 🧑‍💻
Click the "Start Detection" button and allow access to your webcam. The app will start detecting your posture in real time!

Step 7: Get feedback on your posture 🧘‍♀️
The app will display:

Your posture status (Good/Bad)
Neck angle
A timer for bad posture duration
Audio alert after 2 minutes of bad posture
Troubleshooting tips 🛠️
If something isn't working:

No webcam found: Check your camera connection or change the camera index in the code.
Sound issues: Verify the sound file exists and check your system audio settings.
MediaPipe errors: Ensure good lighting conditions and camera positioning.
Contributing to the project 🤝
Feel free to contribute! Open a PR if you have improvements or fixes to share.


